WEBVTT

00:03.000 --> 00:05.400
(folk song playing )

00:05.300 --> 00:08.300
¶ I wanna die ¶

00:10.000 --> 00:13.700
¶ I wanna die ¶

00:14.700 --> 00:19.300
¶ Down south Louisiana ¶

00:19.200 --> 00:22.900
¶ And grey evening sky.¶

00:22.800 --> 00:24.500
Woman:
June 21st.

00:24.500 --> 00:26.800
Exile to Siberia.

00:26.800 --> 00:29.400
I mean, New Jersey.

00:29.300 --> 00:31.300
Is there a difference?

00:31.300 --> 00:33.300
I can't tell.

00:33.300 --> 00:35.800
Isn't Siberia the place
they send you to die?

00:35.700 --> 00:37.700
And from my experience

00:37.700 --> 00:39.800
Ocean Grove isn't that much different.

00:41.300 --> 00:44.100
I think the median age is 85

00:44.100 --> 00:47.900
with the life expectancy of 86.

00:47.700 --> 00:50.000
Sounds about right to me.

00:51.800 --> 00:53.300
Thanks, Mom.

00:53.300 --> 00:55.900
Thank you for buying me
a one-way ticket to hell.

00:56.800 --> 00:59.700
I mean,
Grams' and Gramps' mausoleum.

00:59.600 --> 01:02.100
where it always smells like
desiccated socks.

01:03.400 --> 01:06.200
Oh, I'm sure they're thrilled too.

01:06.200 --> 01:10.400
It'll just be one great summer
of Chinese torture for all of us.

01:11.400 --> 01:13.900
Who cares anyway?

01:13.900 --> 01:15.900
Nobody.

01:15.800 --> 01:19.000
Actually, maybe Ocean Grove
is the perfect place for me.

01:18.900 --> 01:21.300
In fact, when I get off this bus

01:21.200 --> 01:24.000
I should just walk over to the pier
and jump,

01:23.900 --> 01:26.300
end it all.

01:26.300 --> 01:29.100
Goodbye, world.
Goodbye, New Jersey.

01:29.100 --> 01:32.300
The truth is, if I weren't around,

01:32.100 --> 01:35.900
it would solve everyone's problems.

01:35.800 --> 01:38.900
Mom could really focus
on saving marriage number nine.

01:38.800 --> 01:40.800
And my grandmother--

01:40.700 --> 01:43.400
well, she could spend
her whole summer

01:43.300 --> 01:46.000
making those seashell
thingies she makes.

01:45.900 --> 01:47.900
And Gramps could finally finish

01:47.900 --> 01:49.700
fixing up that boat of his.

01:49.700 --> 01:53.300
Yeah, Grams definitely wouldn't care
if I weren't around.

01:53.200 --> 01:56.500
I swear she has some serious
anxiety issues.

01:56.400 --> 01:59.100
Maybe I should give her
some of my pills.

01:59.100 --> 02:01.100
That's what I should do--

02:01.100 --> 02:03.200
make it easy on everyone.

02:03.100 --> 02:05.500
If I weren't here,
their lives would be better.

02:05.500 --> 02:08.600
There's only one person
who might actually care,

02:08.500 --> 02:11.600
but Dad isn't around anymore.

