02:30.200 --> 02:32.800
( man snoring )

02:49.000 --> 02:51.400
( coughing )

02:56.500 --> 02:58.800
Buses suck, huh?

03:05.600 --> 03:08.400
Great. Hello, New Jersey!

03:08.300 --> 03:10.500
Good times, good times.

03:10.500 --> 03:12.300
Hi, sweetie.

03:13.300 --> 03:16.000
Greta, how nice to see you.

03:16.000 --> 03:20.900
Gramps, Grams, hi.

03:20.700 --> 03:23.800
You folks don't look so bad,

03:23.700 --> 03:25.300
all things considered.

03:25.300 --> 03:27.300
Hello to you too, Greta.

03:27.200 --> 03:29.800
Yeah, hello hello.

03:29.700 --> 03:32.600
We all know why I'm here.
No need to act thrilled about it.

03:53.100 --> 03:55.600
We're glad to have you here, honey.
We really are.

03:55.600 --> 03:59.900
Yeah, well, I didn't really plan
on spending my summer in Jersey,

03:59.800 --> 04:03.700
in what might as well be
a nursing home.

04:05.300 --> 04:09.400
Gramps: Well, I guess you're glad
to be out of school for the summer, right?

04:09.300 --> 04:11.800
If I cared one microbe
about school,

04:11.600 --> 04:15.600
I guess yeah, it'd be some kind
of a relief.

04:15.500 --> 04:18.000
Your mother said
you were on the honor roll all year.

04:17.899 --> 04:19.500
That's terrific.

04:19.399 --> 04:21.500
You should be proud of yourself.
You'll get into a good college.

04:21.399 --> 04:22.600
I'm not going to college.

04:22.600 --> 04:24.700
Of course you're going
to college.

04:24.600 --> 04:27.900
The fact is that I'm gonna kill myself
before I turn 18,

04:27.800 --> 04:31.800
so that doesn't really leave much time
for an undergraduate degree.

04:31.700 --> 04:34.100
I assume that you understand

04:34.000 --> 04:36.300
that a joke is supposed
to be funny.

04:36.200 --> 04:38.600
It's not a joke.

04:39.500 --> 04:44.000
See, I've been making this list
of all the different ways you can die--

04:43.900 --> 04:45.700
self-immolation,

04:45.700 --> 04:47.200
falling from a great height.

04:47.200 --> 04:49.400
I don't know about electrocution.

04:49.400 --> 04:52.700
I hear that your heart actually cooks
and you puke up your melted guts.

04:52.600 --> 04:55.800
All right, Greta, just stop.
Just stop right now.

04:55.800 --> 04:58.100
Well, at the same time,
I've been making this list

04:58.000 --> 04:59.800
of things that I want to do
before I die.

04:59.800 --> 05:02.100
For instance,
I want to eat a bug

05:02.100 --> 05:04.000
just to say that I did.

05:03.900 --> 05:06.600
I want to get in a fistfight
with a grown man.

05:06.500 --> 05:08.900
Don't ask.

05:08.800 --> 05:11.100
I want to learn
how to really paint,

05:11.100 --> 05:13.600
and maybe get a tattoo.

05:13.500 --> 05:16.300
Anyway, as soon as I choose
my method of death

05:16.200 --> 05:19.800
then I'm gonna cross as much off
my to-do list as I can

05:19.700 --> 05:23.400
and commit some kind of
grizzly suicide.

05:23.300 --> 05:25.900
Voilà.

05:25.800 --> 05:28.500
You won't have Greta
to kick around anymore.

05:44.300 --> 05:46.800
Come on, Greta.

05:48.600 --> 05:51.100
Well, look who it is.

05:51.100 --> 05:54.700
You certainly have grown up
to be quite the pretty young lady

05:54.600 --> 05:56.500
under all that makeup.

05:56.500 --> 05:59.700
Mrs. Wocheski,
same nosy old bag.

05:59.600 --> 06:01.600
What? What's that?

06:01.600 --> 06:04.600
I said, "Isn't this heat a drag?"

06:04.500 --> 06:05.600
A drag?

06:07.100 --> 06:10.000
Hey, did you hear about
that huge hunk of space junk

06:10.000 --> 06:12.300
that landed in some
old lady's home

06:12.200 --> 06:14.400
just about a month ago
right here in Jersey?

06:14.400 --> 06:15.500
Jersey?

06:15.600 --> 06:18.400
( whispering ) The universe is just
loaded with things that we've left up there.

06:18.300 --> 06:20.000
- What?
- And all of a sudden--

06:19.900 --> 06:21.400
- Bam!
- Whaa!

06:21.400 --> 06:23.900
Instantly vaporized.

06:23.900 --> 06:25.200
( barking )

06:26.600 --> 06:29.200
¶ I don't know what to do
about you ¶

06:30.300 --> 06:34.400
I left your things upstairs,
honey.

06:34.300 --> 06:38.400
¶ I learned a lot of rules
from the Bible, baby ¶

06:38.200 --> 06:41.500
¶ But I wonder wonder
what I should do ¶

06:42.300 --> 06:45.300
¶ But I wonder wonder
what I should do ¶

06:46.400 --> 06:50.300
¶ I don't know
why I'm staying with you ¶

06:50.200 --> 06:54.200
¶ If everything they're saying
is true ¶

06:54.100 --> 06:58.300
¶ I heard about you lying
to your mama, baby ¶

06:58.200 --> 07:00.700
¶ And I wonder wonder
what I should do ¶

07:02.200 --> 07:05.000
¶ But I wonder wonder
what I should do. ¶

07:22.900 --> 07:24.900
( cat mewing )

07:24.900 --> 07:27.300
Parnelli.

07:27.200 --> 07:29.300
Hey.

07:30.300 --> 07:33.200
What's it like living with the mummies
of Guanajuato?

07:33.100 --> 07:35.700
Do you ever get used
to that smell?

07:35.600 --> 07:38.000
Hmm?

07:38.000 --> 07:39.900
You don't care,

07:39.800 --> 07:42.400
as long as someone feeds you
and scoops your litter.

07:43.700 --> 07:47.000
It's a pretty good deal,
a life you want anyway.

07:46.900 --> 07:50.000
( teapot whistling )

07:53.600 --> 07:57.000
Katherine: I'm trying not to be
judgmental, Joseph,

07:56.900 --> 07:59.200
but she's a handful.

07:59.200 --> 08:01.700
Joseph: Oh, Katherine,
it's only three months.

08:01.700 --> 08:03.800
September will be here
before you know it.

08:03.800 --> 08:07.200
You don't think
she's serious, do you?

08:07.100 --> 08:10.000
No, I think she's just
being dramatic,

08:09.900 --> 08:12.700
trying to push our buttons.

08:12.600 --> 08:14.900
Yeah, you know who she
reminds me of at that age?

08:14.800 --> 08:16.300
Karen.

08:16.300 --> 08:20.100
Ow. I'm nothing like my mother!

08:20.000 --> 08:22.100
Nothing!

08:33.100 --> 08:36.000
Hey, Gramps,
can I bump a $20?

08:36.799 --> 08:39.100
Mm!

08:39.000 --> 08:41.500
Greta, we have rules
in this house.

08:41.400 --> 08:44.200
I assume your mother
told you about them.

08:44.100 --> 08:45.800
Yeah.

08:45.800 --> 08:47.900
I'm sure she did.

08:47.800 --> 08:50.000
I'm also sure
I wasn't paying attention.

08:49.900 --> 08:52.100
Oh, well,

08:52.000 --> 08:54.200
then listen to me.

08:54.100 --> 08:58.000
Now you can have
a very nice summer here,

08:57.900 --> 09:02.400
but it won't be
without structure and supervision.

09:04.300 --> 09:07.300
Now if you want to have
spending money,

09:07.200 --> 09:09.800
you're going to have to
get a job.

09:09.600 --> 09:12.500
And there will be
a 10:00 PM curfew.

09:12.400 --> 09:16.200
And you're not permitted
beyond the town lines,

09:16.200 --> 09:19.500
especially not to Asbury Park.
That's no place for you.

09:19.300 --> 09:24.300
So does all of that
sound fair to you?

09:29.400 --> 09:31.900
Let me tell you how this works:

09:31.900 --> 09:36.600
I go where I want
when I want with whom I want.

09:36.400 --> 09:39.000
And I don't come home
until I want to.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
Now that's how it works
at Karen's.

09:40.900 --> 09:44.400
So if you've got a problem with it,
take it up with her.

09:44.300 --> 09:47.200
She's the one who dumped me
on you two anyway.

09:47.000 --> 09:50.000
Okay? Let's just do each other
a favor,

09:50.000 --> 09:51.900
stay out of each other's way.

09:51.800 --> 09:54.000
Summer will be over
before we know it.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.300
Deal?

09:57.600 --> 09:59.700
Deal.

10:03.100 --> 10:05.100
( whistles )

10:20.600 --> 10:23.200
Where did you get that?

10:23.200 --> 10:25.800
Oh, yeah.

10:28.000 --> 10:29.800
What does that thing get,

10:29.700 --> 10:32.800
90 yards to a gallon?

10:32.800 --> 10:34.900
Only on a steep downgrade.

10:34.800 --> 10:36.400
Can I borrow it?

10:36.400 --> 10:39.500
Huh-uh. I heard about what happened
when you went to get your driver's license.

10:39.400 --> 10:42.500
That DMV guy
was emotionally unstable, okay?

10:42.400 --> 10:44.900
It was not my driving
that made him cry.

10:44.800 --> 10:46.000
( Joseph guffaws )

10:45.900 --> 10:47.400
I'm serious.

10:47.400 --> 10:49.500
Okay, we'll see
what your mother thinks.

10:49.400 --> 10:51.200
Like she thinks.

10:51.200 --> 10:54.800
I swear she holds the record
for the most blah moments.

10:54.800 --> 10:58.200
She thinks that string theory
has something to do with macramé.

10:58.000 --> 11:01.400
This is the same woman
that gives me advice on boys.

11:01.300 --> 11:04.600
Her husbands are in and out so fast,
I can't even keep track.

11:04.500 --> 11:06.400
What, is this
husband number nine?

11:06.500 --> 11:08.300
Three.

11:08.300 --> 11:10.500
And you can't drive alone
without a license.

11:10.400 --> 11:12.500
It's against the law.

11:12.400 --> 11:14.800
What's the worst
that's gonna happen, Grams?

11:14.700 --> 11:16.000
I die?

11:16.000 --> 11:17.800
No, the worst thing
that can happen

11:17.700 --> 11:19.600
is that you take somebody
with you when you die.

11:25.200 --> 11:27.200
Greta: Ocean Grove.

11:27.100 --> 11:29.400
More like Ocean Grave.

11:29.400 --> 11:32.000
No wonder Mom left this place
when she was 17.

11:31.900 --> 11:34.400
It's so passé.

11:34.400 --> 11:37.200
I'll make her pay for this torture
when I get home.

11:40.100 --> 11:42.900
That is, if I make it home.

11:52.200 --> 11:56.400
Wow. Okay, I'll give it to her--

11:56.200 --> 11:59.000
Grams looked pretty.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.900
( changing channels )

12:57.900 --> 12:59.900
( turns off TV )

13:01.500 --> 13:03.700
( tinkling )

13:13.900 --> 13:15.000
Can I help you?

13:15.100 --> 13:18.300
There's something majorly wrong
with the cable.

13:18.200 --> 13:21.200
I think you ought to call
and light a fire under someone's ass.

13:21.100 --> 13:22.600
We don't have cable.

13:22.700 --> 13:24.700
Wait, say that again.

13:24.600 --> 13:26.100
I said we don't--

13:26.100 --> 13:29.200
What are you wear--?
Oh, look at you.

13:30.500 --> 13:32.600
How do you survive
without cable?

13:32.500 --> 13:34.400
It's really tough, Greta.

13:34.400 --> 13:36.500
Sometimes we cry ourselves
to sleep at night.

13:38.000 --> 13:41.300
You know, you can always
rent videotapes.

13:41.200 --> 13:43.600
Videotapes?

13:43.500 --> 13:47.100
Come on, who lives like this?

13:47.000 --> 13:49.700
Oh, stop the histrionics, Greta,
for goodness' sakes.

13:49.600 --> 13:51.400
There's so much to do
around here.

13:51.300 --> 13:53.300
There's the whole ocean
right there.

13:53.300 --> 13:55.900
Take my bicycle.
Ride along the boardwalk.

13:55.700 --> 13:58.000
Then you won't have time
for TV.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.700
So you want me to sacrifice
reality TV

14:01.600 --> 14:03.900
for purely empirical
experiences?

14:06.100 --> 14:09.100
Yeah, that's my
recommendation.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.400
Fine.

