15:47.000 --> 15:49.400
Greta: They say that drowning
and freezing to death

15:49.400 --> 15:52.500
are the nicest ways to die,
euphoric even.

15:52.500 --> 15:54.400
I wonder how they would
know that.

16:03.800 --> 16:07.700
The way I see it, what does
experience have to do with anything?

16:07.600 --> 16:10.900
I mean, I've been served
by 1000 waitresses

16:10.900 --> 16:12.900
and the job just doesn't
seem that tough.

16:12.800 --> 16:15.600
I'm sure it has its nuances
just like anything else,

16:15.600 --> 16:17.000
but I'll figure it out.

16:17.000 --> 16:18.800
You're soaking wet.

16:18.800 --> 16:20.500
Oh, come on, Lou.

16:20.500 --> 16:23.100
I'd say the wet T-shirt look
definitely trumps experience.

16:23.100 --> 16:24.700
Does he have
all of his shots?

16:25.900 --> 16:28.400
Let me get you an application.

16:28.400 --> 16:31.100
What the hell for?
It's a yes or no decision.

16:31.000 --> 16:32.800
Not really. It's--

16:32.900 --> 16:36.100
Hey, Lou, give her the job.
You're gonna give it to her anyway.

16:35.900 --> 16:37.200
Zip it, Julie.

16:37.200 --> 16:39.100
See, this is how it works--

16:39.100 --> 16:41.400
you ask him something;
he pretends to chew on it.

16:41.300 --> 16:45.100
He can't say no to nobody,
so you got the job. Don't worry about it.

16:45.000 --> 16:46.300
I don't need your help.

16:46.400 --> 16:48.800
I ain't trying to help you.
Hell, I don't even know you.

16:48.700 --> 16:51.800
I'm trying to help my boy.
One more night that he's shorthanded--

16:51.600 --> 16:54.600
he's gonna develop an ulcer
and it's gonna be problematic for all of us.

16:54.600 --> 16:57.200
Get back to the dungeon.

16:57.200 --> 16:59.600
I'm just saying, man.
I'm just saying.

16:59.500 --> 17:02.400
I can start tomorrow.
Would you like me here at 4:00?

17:02.300 --> 17:03.400
Um...

17:03.400 --> 17:05.000
Or how about lunch?

17:05.000 --> 17:07.599
Then I can learn everything.
It'll be all good.

17:07.500 --> 17:08.599
Uh...

17:08.599 --> 17:10.599
Great. See you then.

17:12.800 --> 17:15.599
Hey, that girl's trouble.

17:15.500 --> 17:18.500
I think I just hired her.

17:18.400 --> 17:22.099
( chattering, laughing )

17:22.000 --> 17:24.900
Oh my God, you guys
are still awake?

17:24.800 --> 17:27.900
You do realize
it's past 9:00, right?

17:27.900 --> 17:30.800
You realize
that you missed dinner?

17:30.700 --> 17:32.900
What happened to my dress?

17:32.900 --> 17:35.300
Oh, I went swimming.

17:35.200 --> 17:38.300
New York doesn't use that ocean
as a toilet, do they?

17:38.200 --> 17:40.400
Is my hair starting
to turn green?

17:40.300 --> 17:43.300
Greta, I really don't mind
you wearing my dress.

17:43.200 --> 17:46.600
I do mind you going swimming in it.
Would you take it off, please?

17:46.500 --> 17:48.200
Greta, your mother called.

17:48.200 --> 17:50.900
You were supposed to let her know
you got down here all right.

17:50.900 --> 17:53.400
Well, did you tell her
that I was still alive?

17:53.300 --> 17:56.100
Why don't you tell her?
There's a phone on the piano.

17:56.100 --> 17:58.400
- Are you taking that?
- Yes, I am.

17:58.400 --> 18:01.100
- You're in deep trouble now.
- Come on.

18:01.100 --> 18:03.200
- Gin.
- Oh, no.

18:04.100 --> 18:06.100
It's me.
What do you want?

18:06.100 --> 18:08.500
Karen: I see you survived
the bus trip after all.

18:08.500 --> 18:11.200
I'd rather have ferried
across the River Styx.

18:11.100 --> 18:14.000
Grams told me about your little
to-die list.

18:13.900 --> 18:16.000
You shouldn't scare her
like that.

18:16.000 --> 18:19.000
She doesn't know you well enough
to understand.

18:18.800 --> 18:21.500
How's my old room look?

18:21.400 --> 18:23.600
Does she still have
her seashells everywhere?

18:23.500 --> 18:26.100
It's a shell hole, Mom.

18:27.600 --> 18:30.100
Why are you doing this to me?

18:30.000 --> 18:32.600
Karen: You know why.
We've discussed this.

18:32.500 --> 18:35.000
I am trying
to save my marriage.

18:34.900 --> 18:36.600
You would have better luck

18:36.700 --> 18:39.400
trying to save
the polar ice caps, Mom.

18:40.200 --> 18:43.700
Why is it that your marriage only works
when I'm not there?

18:43.600 --> 18:46.700
Sweetie,

18:46.600 --> 18:50.300
Greta, I know this is tough,
but try to make the best of it.

18:56.400 --> 18:59.400
Take as much time
as you need, okay, Karen?

18:59.300 --> 19:02.500
Sort things out,
shuffle them together,

19:02.500 --> 19:04.400
do whatever the hell it is
you need to do

19:04.400 --> 19:06.300
to try and save
this marriage, okay?

19:06.200 --> 19:09.000
I'm here and I'm fine.
Don't even worry about me.

19:08.900 --> 19:10.400
I'm fine!

