in my head.

27:02.500 --> 27:05.100
I'm just trying
to protect you.

27:05.000 --> 27:06.700
It's a little late.

27:10.300 --> 27:12.800
I'm really tired, Grams.

27:13.600 --> 27:16.000
Good night.

27:19.300 --> 27:21.600
Good night.

27:24.900 --> 27:25.000
Well, I admit
she's a bit of a challenge, but--

27:25.000 --> 27:27.300
Well, I admit
she's a bit of a challenge, but--

27:27.300 --> 27:28.500
What?

27:28.400 --> 27:31.100
A challenge.
I say she's a challenge.

27:31.000 --> 27:34.000
A challenge?
She's a pain in the butt.

27:35.100 --> 27:37.100
Good morning.

27:37.000 --> 27:39.500
Oh, love,

27:39.500 --> 27:43.900
it seems Greta is giving
Mrs. Wocheski some difficulty.

27:43.800 --> 27:46.300
There's no "seems" about it.
She is.

27:46.200 --> 27:50.500
She said Mr. Poodles
was just a mangy rodent

27:50.500 --> 27:53.700
and not a real dog at all.

27:53.600 --> 27:55.800
And then she said
he looks just like me.

27:55.700 --> 27:57.600
Are you sure you heard her
correctly?

27:57.600 --> 27:58.600
What?

27:58.600 --> 28:01.300
I said I'm sure she meant it
in the sweetest possible way.

28:01.200 --> 28:04.300
Oh, she's a menace,
that girl.

28:04.200 --> 28:07.000
You'd better keep
a sharp eye out.

28:06.900 --> 28:09.200
Well, we'll see to it
that she apologizes.

28:09.200 --> 28:12.200
Won't we, dear?

28:12.100 --> 28:13.200
Are you done?

28:13.200 --> 28:14.500
I wish.

28:14.400 --> 28:16.700
- Well, how much longer?
- Just a bit.

28:16.600 --> 28:19.000
Excuse me, is that
your van outside?

28:18.900 --> 28:21.300
Yes, ma'am.
I'm hooking it up right now.

28:21.300 --> 28:23.900
Well, I didn't order any hooking up,
so you just go ahead

28:23.800 --> 28:26.000
and unhook
whatever it is you hooked.

28:26.000 --> 28:28.500
Grams, I'm paying for this.

28:28.400 --> 28:29.700
That's not the point.

28:29.800 --> 28:32.700
You're gonna love this, okay?

28:32.600 --> 28:34.300
I don't want cable.

28:34.200 --> 28:37.000
Look, I'm almost done here,
so if you don't want this--

28:36.900 --> 28:40.800
Grams, it's guaranteed to keep me
out of trouble the whole summer.

28:40.700 --> 28:43.200
And it's not costing you
a thing.

28:46.500 --> 28:48.300
We've got to send her home.

28:48.200 --> 28:50.400
I can't do it.
I just can't take it anymore.

28:50.300 --> 28:53.100
Oh, honey, so she wants
the cable TV.

28:53.000 --> 28:55.000
What's the harm in that?

28:54.900 --> 28:58.300
Katherine: That's the point.
She does whatever she wants to do.

28:58.200 --> 28:59.900
She has no boundaries.

28:59.800 --> 29:02.700
Karen's always been
too permissive with her.

29:02.700 --> 29:05.000
Okay, that'll do it.

29:05.000 --> 29:06.200
Finally.

29:06.100 --> 29:07.800
This here is your remote.
What you do is--

29:07.800 --> 29:10.200
Yeah, I got it, okay?
Scram.

29:10.200 --> 29:13.100
All right, just--

29:12.900 --> 29:15.300
I just need a signature here.

29:15.300 --> 29:17.400
- ( flipping channels )
- Ma'am?

29:19.100 --> 29:20.500
Sir?

29:23.100 --> 29:25.800
- I just need a signature.
- Okay, I got it.

29:28.900 --> 29:31.300
- Hey.
- I told Mrs. Wocheski

29:31.300 --> 29:34.300
that you would apologize
for that smart-alecky remark

29:34.100 --> 29:35.300
you made about her dog.

29:35.400 --> 29:37.100
Now please go do it.

29:37.100 --> 29:39.800
I can't believe you would
sell out your own granddaughter

29:39.800 --> 29:41.100
to that old blue-hair.

29:41.100 --> 29:43.100
It's not even blue
in a good way.

29:43.100 --> 29:44.400
Go.

29:45.500 --> 29:47.300
Now.

30:04.700 --> 30:07.400
We thought we heard
someone at the door.

30:07.400 --> 30:10.600
You ratted me out
to my grandparents.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.500
I most certainly did.

30:12.500 --> 30:15.100
And I believe you owe me
an apology.

30:16.600 --> 30:18.900
You know,

30:18.800 --> 30:21.500
I noticed you keep those windows
pretty much open all the time.

30:21.400 --> 30:24.000
Of course I do.
The breeze is healthy.

30:24.000 --> 30:25.500
Yeah?

30:25.500 --> 30:27.500
What time do you go to bed
around usually,

30:27.500 --> 30:29.800
7:30, 8:00-ish?

30:29.700 --> 30:31.100
What are you getting at?

30:31.100 --> 30:34.200
( chuckles )

30:34.200 --> 30:35.700
You don't scare me.

30:35.700 --> 30:37.700
Mm-hmm.

30:41.200 --> 30:43.200
You don't scare me.

30:44.400 --> 30:46.400
( dog yapping )

30:52.200 --> 30:54.700
( patrons chattering )

30:56.000 --> 30:58.500
Give me just one second here.

30:58.400 --> 31:00.400
Uh, okay.

31:08.900 --> 31:10.400
How's the perch?

31:10.300 --> 31:12.000
How should I know?

31:12.100 --> 31:13.400
I'm sorry?

31:13.300 --> 31:16.100
It's perch.
I'm sure it's fresh.

31:16.000 --> 31:19.200
I'm sure it tastes
how perch usually does.

31:19.200 --> 31:22.800
I can't afford to eat here,
so how should I know?

31:22.700 --> 31:25.100
There's no need to be rude.

31:25.100 --> 31:26.200
Woman: Table 12.

31:26.300 --> 31:28.000
Man: Can I get a side
of horseradish?

31:30.300 --> 31:32.600
What's the perch taste like?

31:32.500 --> 31:34.600
What?

31:34.500 --> 31:36.500
The perch-- how is it?

31:36.500 --> 31:39.700
It's all right,
but the catfish is the business.

31:39.600 --> 31:42.500
Yeah? What's that
taste like?

31:43.700 --> 31:46.400
Are you telling me you've never
tried fish before?

31:46.400 --> 31:47.900
Yeah, I have.

31:47.800 --> 31:50.000
Okay, I'm not talking
out of the box or the can.

31:50.000 --> 31:52.700
What kind of wonk
has never tasted fish before?

31:56.700 --> 32:00.200
Okay, maybe not.

32:00.100 --> 32:02.700
Come around here.
I'm gonna show you what it tastes like.

32:02.700 --> 32:04.200
Come on.

32:06.800 --> 32:10.600
Okay, now this right here
is perch, all right?

32:18.500 --> 32:21.000
Now hold on.
Stay here.

32:23.400 --> 32:25.900
Now this is catfish,

32:25.900 --> 32:29.200
Cajun blackened, okay?

32:29.100 --> 32:30.600
Okay.

32:30.500 --> 32:32.800
It's my favorite.

32:35.300 --> 32:38.400
Mm.

32:38.400 --> 32:39.900
You made that?

32:39.800 --> 32:42.100
Yeah.

32:45.800 --> 32:48.200
Well, that is
surprisingly edible.

32:48.200 --> 32:50.400
Well, I'm glad you like it.

32:52.100 --> 32:54.100
Man: Hey, Julie.

32:54.100 --> 32:56.100
Man #2: I need another special.

33:00.500 --> 33:01.900
You don't want the perch.

33:02.000 --> 33:03.300
What's this?

33:03.200 --> 33:04.400
Catfish.

33:04.400 --> 33:06.400
But I wanted the perch.

33:06.300 --> 33:09.300
No, trust me,
you want the catfish.

33:09.300 --> 33:11.500
The perch is all right,

33:11.400 --> 33:14.000
the catfish is the business.

33:19.800 --> 33:21.800
( distant siren wailing )

33:30.700 --> 33:33.500
You know, it's really gonna be
really hard for you to ride that bike

33:33.300 --> 33:35.300
with my foot
shoved up your ass.

33:35.400 --> 33:37.400
Wow.

33:37.300 --> 33:40.400
Oh, it's you. I thought you were
these guys from the other night.

33:40.300 --> 33:43.200
- You ever let it down?
- What?

33:43.000 --> 33:45.000
Your force field.

33:45.000 --> 33:47.000
You know, you walk around
all up in your own shit

33:47.100 --> 33:49.400
like you ain't got no time
for nobody else's goodness.

33:49.400 --> 33:52.100
How does somebody get close enough
to give you what you need?

33:52.000 --> 33:54.000
I don't need anything.

33:54.000 --> 33:55.700
Everybody needs something.

33:55.600 --> 33:58.500
As of right now, seems like
you might need a ride.

33:58.500 --> 34:00.400
On that?

34:00.300 --> 34:01.800
Yeah.

34:01.800 --> 34:03.700
I don't think two bodies
can fit on that.

34:03.800 --> 34:05.700
What, is it, like,
your little brother's bike?

34:05.700 --> 34:08.300
Okay, let me tell you something
about this right here.

34:08.199 --> 34:10.699
This is a masterpiece
of engineering.

34:10.699 --> 34:13.400
This is the product
of my love and sweat.

34:13.300 --> 34:15.600
And it can and will prove you wrong.
But as of right now,

34:15.500 --> 34:19.300
I don't think I even want
to let you on this thing.

34:19.199 --> 34:23.199
I mean, unless-- and I mean,
only if you promise to be sweet.

34:25.199 --> 34:27.199
Promise.

34:28.100 --> 34:30.400
Are you always
that sensitive?

34:30.300 --> 34:32.300
I mean, didn't your mama
breastfeed you?

34:32.300 --> 34:35.000
Okay, that would be classified
as sour in my kitchen.

34:35.000 --> 34:38.199
But I'm gonna pretend
that didn't happen.

34:38.100 --> 34:40.100
Okay? Come on.

34:50.000 --> 34:53.300
Now you promise
to be sweet, right?

34:53.100 --> 34:55.500
Yeah.

34:55.400 --> 34:57.400
I promise.

