I gotta get out of here.

57:03.600 --> 57:06.300
What are you doing?
Julie, Julie.

57:06.300 --> 57:09.300
Hey, get out of there.

57:09.200 --> 57:12.700
Come on, get down.
On the ground. On the ground.

57:12.500 --> 57:14.200
I didn't do anything.

57:14.300 --> 57:15.800
Shit.

57:15.700 --> 57:19.000
Come on, junior.
Get up, get up.

57:19.000 --> 57:21.100
Just one second, man.
I didn't do nothing.

57:21.100 --> 57:23.900
- Wait wait, hold on, hold on.
- Easy now.

57:23.800 --> 57:26.400
Mrs. O'Donnell, you gotta tell them.
They made a mistake.

57:26.300 --> 57:27.900
What's going on here?

57:27.900 --> 57:30.000
A neighbor spotted this individual
climbing up your trellis, ma'am.

57:30.000 --> 57:32.400
- Ma'am, do you know this person?
- Yes, of course.

57:32.300 --> 57:34.300
I thought you were through
with stealing.

57:34.300 --> 57:37.300
I wasn't stealing anything.
It's a mix-up. They made a mistake.

57:37.200 --> 57:38.700
Leave him alone.

57:38.700 --> 57:42.100
Just one second, man.
I didn't do nothing.

57:42.000 --> 57:45.000
Grams, tell them to stop, please.
He's gonna be in so much trouble.

57:45.000 --> 57:46.900
- What is he doing here?
- I invited him here.

57:46.800 --> 57:50.300
- To do what exactly?
- What's going on here?

57:50.100 --> 57:51.700
Gramps, please
make them stop.

57:51.800 --> 57:54.500
Okay, that's it. I've had it.
I'm calling your mother right now.

57:54.400 --> 57:56.900
You're insane.

57:56.800 --> 57:58.700
- Look, he didn't do anything.
- No, back inside.

57:58.600 --> 58:00.900
Joseph: Katherine, don't get Karen
all riled up.

58:00.900 --> 58:03.000
Gramps, they're gonna
take him in.

58:03.000 --> 58:04.700
- I've got to call her mother.
- You have to go tell them.

58:04.700 --> 58:07.100
He didn't do anything wrong.
I promise.

58:07.100 --> 58:09.200
- He crawled through my window.
- Shut up, Grams.

58:09.100 --> 58:11.100
- Don't talk to her that way.
- Please, it's not fair.

58:11.100 --> 58:13.100
You're not helping things.
Now listen to me.

58:13.000 --> 58:15.000
Go upstairs
and let me deal with this.

58:15.000 --> 58:17.500
I will take care of this.
Yes yes, right now.

58:17.500 --> 58:20.100
I will take care of this.
I will deal with it. Go on, go on.

58:20.000 --> 58:21.800
Go on.

58:21.800 --> 58:24.100
Oh, that girl--
she is totally out of control.

58:24.000 --> 58:26.000
I mean, just once
she's got to learn

58:26.000 --> 58:28.400
that she can't have everything
her own way.

58:30.700 --> 58:33.900
She's your family, Katherine.
She's your flesh and blood.

58:33.900 --> 58:37.500
She's not some enemy
you have to defeat.

58:47.000 --> 58:50.700
I apologize for all this,
Mr. O'Donnell.

58:50.600 --> 58:53.200
And I hope I didn't get Greta
in too much trouble.

58:53.100 --> 58:55.400
Thanks.

58:55.300 --> 58:57.800
And I think you got it backwards.
I think she's the one

58:57.800 --> 58:59.400
who got you in trouble.

58:59.300 --> 59:02.200
I like her, you know.
I really like Greta

59:02.100 --> 59:06.100
and she's worth it,

59:06.000 --> 59:08.800
but I'm worried about her,
you know?

59:08.700 --> 59:11.000
Does she ever talk to you about--?

59:11.000 --> 59:15.000
She's got that little notebook
she carries around.

59:14.800 --> 59:17.000
Do you--?

59:27.200 --> 59:30.000
Greta ever say anything to you
about her father?

59:29.900 --> 59:33.600
She doesn't talk too much
about personal stuff, you know.

59:33.400 --> 59:36.900
Well, it's something we don't
talk about very much in this family either,

59:36.800 --> 59:39.400
but I think you've earned the right
to know about it.

59:41.300 --> 59:44.700
Greta's father killed himself.

59:46.200 --> 59:48.500
She was just a little kid,

59:48.500 --> 59:50.400
five, six years old.

59:50.400 --> 59:54.100
He took his shotgun
and stuck it in his mouth.

59:55.400 --> 59:57.400
She was there.
She walked in on him.

59:59.000 --> 01:00:01.200
You know, I don't know

01:00:01.200 --> 01:00:03.200
how much of it
she remembers,

01:00:03.200 --> 01:00:06.700
how much
she carries around with her,

01:00:06.600 --> 01:00:08.800
but here she is,
all grown up,

01:00:08.800 --> 01:00:11.200
and writing that list.

01:00:13.600 --> 01:00:16.100
You know, it may be a phase
she's going through.

01:00:16.100 --> 01:00:19.600
It may be just some idea
that she has to reckon with,

01:00:19.500 --> 01:00:23.100
but I think--

01:00:22.900 --> 01:00:25.700
I think it's our job

01:00:25.600 --> 01:00:27.700
to try and help her
through it.

01:00:27.600 --> 01:00:30.100
Wow.

01:00:31.200 --> 01:00:33.200
Yeah.

01:00:34.200 --> 01:00:36.300
Well, go on home.

01:00:36.200 --> 01:00:38.200
Get some sleep.

01:00:38.200 --> 01:00:40.600
Thank you, sir.

01:00:41.900 --> 01:00:43.900
- Hey, Julie.
- Yeah?

01:00:43.900 --> 01:00:45.500
Do you get seasick?

01:00:48.300 --> 01:00:52.400
¶ If life is like a mountain,
did you, did you not fall? ¶

01:00:52.300 --> 01:00:56.300
¶ I have missed you
since I was five ¶

01:00:56.200 --> 01:00:59.800
¶ I don't recall your eyes,
but your hands I do recall ¶

01:00:59.700 --> 01:01:04.600
¶ And I know how you smelled
when you were alive ¶

01:01:04.500 --> 01:01:07.400
¶ You've died ¶

01:01:07.200 --> 01:01:10.800
¶ Like we're all gonna go
someday ¶

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:15.000
¶ You've died ¶

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:19.200
¶ I was five
and I wish you'd stayed ¶

01:01:34.800 --> 01:01:38.200
¶ You've died ¶

01:01:38.100 --> 01:01:42.900
¶ I was five
and I wish you'd stayed. ¶

01:01:55.100 --> 01:01:57.500
Yeah, this is great.

01:01:57.400 --> 01:01:59.800
I feel all preppy and shit.

01:01:59.700 --> 01:02:02.100
Why are we here?

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:04.600
Your grandfather's
a good guy, you know.

01:02:04.500 --> 01:02:07.300
This means a lot to him.

01:02:07.200 --> 01:02:10.300
Come on, it's not that bad,
though, right?

01:02:11.900 --> 01:02:14.300
Hey,

01:02:14.200 --> 01:02:16.500
remember that stuff

01:02:16.500 --> 01:02:18.500
that you said in my room
the other night?

01:02:18.400 --> 01:02:19.600
Yeah, I remember.

01:02:19.700 --> 01:02:21.700
Did you mean that?

01:02:21.700 --> 01:02:24.400
Have I lied to you yet?

01:02:24.300 --> 01:02:26.600
I don't know.

01:02:26.600 --> 01:02:29.300
Hey, Julie,
want to take the helm?

01:02:30.600 --> 01:02:32.100
Go ahead.

01:02:32.100 --> 01:02:34.400
All right, I'm coming.

01:02:42.500 --> 01:02:44.800
Just keep her
in a straight line.

01:02:51.300 --> 01:02:55.100
Katherine: I love it.
It's wonderful.

01:02:55.900 --> 01:02:58.900
¶ Come with me ¶

01:03:00.300 --> 01:03:05.300
¶ Come with me ¶

01:03:05.200 --> 01:03:08.000
¶ On a voyage ¶

01:03:07.900 --> 01:03:10.400
¶ To the bottom ¶

01:03:10.300 --> 01:03:12.800
¶ Of the sea ¶

01:03:16.900 --> 01:03:20.500
¶ In a sea ¶

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:25.800
¶ Of blue-green ¶

01:03:25.700 --> 01:03:28.600
¶ We will find love ¶

01:03:28.600 --> 01:03:30.900
¶ At the bottom ¶

01:03:30.800 --> 01:03:33.500
¶ Of the sea ¶

01:03:37.200 --> 01:03:41.800
¶ Unbelievable, inconceivable ¶

01:03:41.800 --> 01:03:46.300
¶ Fantastic it will seem ¶

01:03:47.200 --> 01:03:50.500
¶ But we'll be the first ¶

01:03:50.400 --> 01:03:52.700
¶ The very first ¶

01:03:52.700 --> 01:03:57.700
¶ To live such a strange
new dream ¶

01:03:59.300 --> 01:04:02.100
¶ Come with me.¶

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:04.200
Greta.

01:04:11.100 --> 01:04:13.500
Greta.

01:04:39.800 --> 01:04:41.100
There they are.

01:04:44.500 --> 01:04:46.500
Greta.

01:04:55.700 --> 01:04:58.000
I've got you.
I've got you.

01:05:01.400 --> 01:05:05.200
Okay, right there, right there.

01:05:05.100 --> 01:05:08.500
Are you all right?

01:05:08.400 --> 01:05:10.400
Yeah. Are you okay?

01:05:10.300 --> 01:05:12.300
- Are you okay, honey?
- My head.

01:05:12.300 --> 01:05:14.800
You hit your head?
Let me see it.

01:05:14.700 --> 01:05:17.600
Turn it.

01:05:17.600 --> 01:05:19.700
Joseph: It's not bleeding.

01:05:19.600 --> 01:05:21.300
Grams.

01:05:22.600 --> 01:05:24.800
Grams.

01:05:24.700 --> 01:05:27.200
Katherine, Katherine.

01:05:27.200 --> 01:05:29.500
Are you all right?

01:05:29.400 --> 01:05:32.000
- Grams.
- I'm gonna get on the radio.

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:35.300
Grams, hey.

01:05:35.200 --> 01:05:37.500
( P.A. chatter )

01:05:46.500 --> 01:05:48.900
It was a mild heart attack.
She's okay.

01:05:48.800 --> 01:05:51.200
She's gonna have to be
on medication from now on, though.

01:05:51.100 --> 01:05:54.100
But she's okay.
They want to keep her here tonight

01:05:54.100 --> 01:05:55.800
and run some more tests.

01:05:55.700 --> 01:05:58.200
I'm gonna stay with her
until she goes to sleep.

01:05:58.200 --> 01:06:00.000
You two go on home,

01:06:00.100 --> 01:06:02.300
get out of this
air conditioning.

01:06:25.900 --> 01:06:28.400
( thunder rumbling )

01:06:38.300 --> 01:06:41.400
Hey, here.

01:06:44.300 --> 01:06:46.300
You're not gonna stay?

01:06:46.300 --> 01:06:50.800
No, you can check me off
that list of yours.

01:06:50.600 --> 01:06:52.600
I'm done.

01:06:52.500 --> 01:06:54.800
What?

01:06:54.700 --> 01:06:57.100
What are you talking about?

01:06:59.200 --> 01:07:01.500
Are you serious?

01:07:01.400 --> 01:07:03.000
You really don't get it?

01:07:08.500 --> 01:07:11.400
Reggie Spiegel,

01:07:11.300 --> 01:07:13.300
my roommate in juvie.

01:07:15.100 --> 01:07:17.600
One morning, Mother's Day...

01:07:20.300 --> 01:07:24.500
I found him hanging
by an electric cord.

01:07:29.300 --> 01:07:32.900
I didn't see it coming
'cause he didn't mouth off about it.

01:07:32.800 --> 01:07:35.200
He didn't want to be saved.

01:07:35.200 --> 01:07:37.200
See, you knew I'd jump in
after you

01:07:37.100 --> 01:07:39.700
'cause you didn't want to die.

01:07:39.600 --> 01:07:41.700
You just wanted that drama.

01:07:41.700 --> 01:07:44.500
- No, l--
- What you did was serious.

01:07:44.400 --> 01:07:46.800
And it affects people.

01:07:46.700 --> 01:07:49.300
It affects me.

01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:54.300
I wish I could help you,
'cause you need it.

01:07:55.200 --> 01:07:57.600
But I'm not going
overboard for you.

01:07:57.500 --> 01:08:00.900
I got my own shit.
I'm doing my own thing.

01:08:00.800 --> 01:08:03.300
You know?

01:08:58.899 --> 01:09:02.100
"April 10th, 1962.

01:09:04.200 --> 01:09:06.200
My sweet sweet Joseph,

01:09:06.200 --> 01:09:09.000
you set sail
less than an hour ago

01:09:08.899 --> 01:09:11.399
and I'm kicking myself already.

01:09:11.300 --> 01:09:13.800
Please forgive me.

01:09:13.700 --> 01:09:16.100
I only treated you that way

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:18.899
because I was mad
about you leaving.

01:09:18.800 --> 01:09:20.800
I've been silly,

01:09:20.700 --> 01:09:24.000
prone to capriciousness.

01:09:23.899 --> 01:09:27.300
I'm mad at myself

01:09:27.200 --> 01:09:30.100
for wasting our last
moments together,

01:09:30.100 --> 01:09:32.500
for not telling you

01:09:32.399 --> 01:09:34.700
how I really feel.

01:09:34.700 --> 01:09:37.300
I love you

01:09:37.300 --> 01:09:41.600
and I've missed my chance
to tell you in person.

01:09:41.399 --> 01:09:44.100
If something happens to you,
I'll just die.

01:09:45.700 --> 01:09:48.000
I miss you, Joseph.

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:50.899
Promise you'll come home safely.

01:09:50.800 --> 01:09:53.200
Forever yours, Katherine."

01:10:25.600 --> 01:10:28.300
Grams.

01:10:48.300 --> 01:10:50.600
( tinkling )

01:12:01.100 --> 01:12:03.900
Okay, close your eyes.

01:12:03.800 --> 01:12:06.300
Katherine: Can I trust you?

01:12:07.200 --> 01:12:10.300
Okay, this way.

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:14.000
Can I open my eyes yet?

01:12:13.900 --> 01:12:16.100
Mm, okay.

01:12:19.400 --> 01:12:25.000
Oh, you didn't have to
do that, Greta.

01:12:24.900 --> 01:12:27.000
Those flowers
are expensive.

01:12:30.100 --> 01:12:33.500
Can't you see that I'm trying
to say I'm sorry?

01:12:37.000 --> 01:12:40.100
Well, then say it.

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:42.900
I just did.

01:12:42.900 --> 01:12:44.500
No.

01:12:44.400 --> 01:12:47.400
You don't even know
what you're sorry for.

01:12:47.400 --> 01:12:50.200
I'm fighting to save my life

01:12:50.100 --> 01:12:53.400
and you're trying
to throw yours away.

01:12:53.200 --> 01:12:55.200
Now why is that?

01:12:57.900 --> 01:13:00.900
'Cause...

01:13:00.800 --> 01:13:04.400
I want to be
like the girl in this picture,

01:13:04.300 --> 01:13:06.700
young and alive.

01:13:06.600 --> 01:13:09.100
I haven't seen this picture since--

01:13:10.800 --> 01:13:12.900
I wasn't any older
than you there.

01:13:12.800 --> 01:13:16.000
You look like a totally
different person,

01:13:15.900 --> 01:13:18.800
so happy.
Don't you miss that?

01:13:18.700 --> 01:13:21.500
Well, no.

01:13:21.300 --> 01:13:24.500
You're telling me
that you wouldn't jump at the chance

01:13:24.400 --> 01:13:26.400
if you could turn
the clock back?

01:13:26.400 --> 01:13:28.200
( chuckles ) No.

01:13:28.300 --> 01:13:30.700
I wouldn't.

01:13:31.600 --> 01:13:34.000
You see...

01:13:35.300 --> 01:13:38.000
I was a different person then.

01:13:37.800 --> 01:13:41.600
I didn't know anything
about the world or myself.

01:13:41.600 --> 01:13:45.900
I had no perspective.

01:13:48.900 --> 01:13:51.800
This was a long time ago.

01:13:54.100 --> 01:13:56.100
And every day since then,

01:13:56.100 --> 01:13:58.600
every experience I've had,

01:13:58.500 --> 01:14:01.200
every person I've met

01:14:01.100 --> 01:14:05.700
has carved an impression on me.

01:14:06.500 --> 01:14:09.800
You know, this girl, this child--

01:14:09.700 --> 01:14:12.700
she's just a fraction
of what I've become--

01:14:12.600 --> 01:14:16.300
a wife, a mother,
a grandmother--

01:14:16.200 --> 01:14:17.700
me.

01:14:17.600 --> 01:14:20.100
Oh, honey,
you have no idea

01:14:20.000 --> 01:14:23.200
what's ahead of you.

01:14:23.100 --> 01:14:27.100
It's all such an incredible
adventure.

01:14:31.600 --> 01:14:34.300
Do you have a picture of my dad?

01:14:35.900 --> 01:14:38.700
I just want to know
what he looks like.

01:14:38.600 --> 01:14:41.800
You've never seen
a picture of your father?

01:14:42.600 --> 01:14:44.600
No.

01:14:46.500 --> 01:14:48.900
Sweetheart.

01:14:52.600 --> 01:14:54.900
( horn honks )

01:15:01.400 --> 01:15:03.400
What are they doing here?

01:15:03.400 --> 01:15:05.400
Mom.

01:15:05.300 --> 01:15:07.700
Hiya, all.

01:15:07.600 --> 01:15:10.100
Are you okay?

01:15:10.100 --> 01:15:12.800
Shouldn't you be
sitting down or something?

01:15:12.700 --> 01:15:14.700
- I'm fine, dear. Hello.
- I'm so sorry.

01:15:14.600 --> 01:15:17.200
What are you doing here?

01:15:17.100 --> 01:15:19.300
Gramps, what are they
doing here?

01:15:19.200 --> 01:15:21.500
Greta, go inside
and get your things.

01:15:21.400 --> 01:15:23.000
I don't want to go home
with you.

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:24.800
We're not taking you
home, Greta.

01:15:24.800 --> 01:15:27.900
Then why are you he--?

01:15:27.800 --> 01:15:30.900
You're gonna send me
to that boot camp.

01:15:32.300 --> 01:15:33.700
Go get your things, Greta.

01:15:33.700 --> 01:15:36.100
Wait a minute.
What's this boot camp stuff?

01:15:36.100 --> 01:15:38.700
No, it's a special
summer camp

01:15:38.600 --> 01:15:41.200
for kids like her,

01:15:41.100 --> 01:15:42.800
to straighten her out.

01:15:42.700 --> 01:15:46.000
Gramps, why didn't you tell me
that they were coming?

01:15:45.900 --> 01:15:48.000
I asked your grandfather
not to say anything.

01:15:47.900 --> 01:15:50.000
We didn't want you
running off or something.

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:52.700
- Greta.
- Edgar: Come on now.

01:15:53.600 --> 01:15:55.600
Karen: Greta.

01:16:05.300 --> 01:16:08.200
My mom is here.

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:11.400
She's gonna send me away
to some boot camp place.

01:16:11.400 --> 01:16:13.300
What am I gonna do?

01:16:13.300 --> 01:16:15.600
What can you do?

01:16:15.500 --> 01:16:18.000
There's got to be something.

01:16:18.000 --> 01:16:21.000
I guess you could
check the camp out,

01:16:20.900 --> 01:16:22.400
see what it's all about.

01:16:22.300 --> 01:16:25.200
You think I'm screwed up
and that place is gonna save me?

01:16:25.200 --> 01:16:26.700
Yeah, you're screwed up.

01:16:28.400 --> 01:16:30.700
But that place can't fix you.

01:16:30.700 --> 01:16:32.300
Only you can fix you.

01:16:32.200 --> 01:16:35.300
If that's not what you want,
it ain't gonna happen.

01:16:43.000 --> 01:16:45.700
I'm really sorry.

01:16:45.600 --> 01:16:48.100
Well, that's a start.

01:16:59.400 --> 01:17:02.300
- You smell like food.
- Yeah.

01:17:02.300 --> 01:17:04.300
Yeah.

01:17:10.400 --> 01:17:14.100
Call me when you get it all
figured out, okay?

01:17:18.100 --> 01:17:20.100
All right.

01:17:29.700 --> 01:17:32.000
Have a nice walk?

01:17:31.900 --> 01:17:34.500
Did Mom leave?

01:17:34.400 --> 01:17:36.800
She's here now,
so come on back.

01:17:36.800 --> 01:17:38.800
You all finished
with your little tantrum?

01:17:38.800 --> 01:17:40.300
What are you doing
with my stuff?

01:17:40.300 --> 01:17:42.500
I packed your things.
You've wasted enough time already.

01:17:42.400 --> 01:17:44.900
I don't want to go.
Please, please let me stay.

01:17:44.900 --> 01:17:46.900
Your grandmother
does not want you here.

01:17:46.900 --> 01:17:49.800
- That's not true.
- That's what you told me last week.

01:17:49.800 --> 01:17:51.900
"There's no winning with her,"
you said.

01:17:51.800 --> 01:17:53.300
Did I say that?

01:17:53.300 --> 01:17:55.900
Well, that was then
and this is now.

01:17:55.700 --> 01:17:58.300
And if Greta wants to stay,
I would quite like to have her.

01:17:58.200 --> 01:18:00.700
- I'm staying.
- No, you're not.

01:18:00.700 --> 01:18:02.400
- Mom.
- Shh.

01:18:02.400 --> 01:18:06.000
- Greta, let go.
- Be careful there. Be careful.

01:18:05.900 --> 01:18:07.200
Mom.

01:18:07.200 --> 01:18:09.400
- Quiet down and give me the bag.
- What's wrong with you?

01:18:09.300 --> 01:18:11.000
- Greta, stop it.
- Edgar: What's going on?

01:18:10.900 --> 01:18:12.600
- Mom, please.
- Stop making a scene.

01:18:12.500 --> 01:18:14.300
- Edgar: What are you doing?
- Edgar, I could use some help.

01:18:14.400 --> 01:18:16.300
- Be careful. Don't hurt her.
- Come on now.

01:18:16.300 --> 01:18:18.400
Mrs. Wocheski: What the hell
is going on over there?

01:18:18.400 --> 01:18:20.800
All right, just stop.
Everybody just stop.

01:18:23.800 --> 01:18:26.200
( blaring )

01:18:29.500 --> 01:18:33.200
Greta, get up.

01:18:33.100 --> 01:18:35.500
Please, Katherine, sit down.

01:18:35.500 --> 01:18:37.500
I'm sick of all this.

01:18:37.400 --> 01:18:39.700
I'm tired of all this screaming
and yelling and fighting

01:18:39.700 --> 01:18:41.600
and the police on my porch
in the middle of the night

01:18:41.500 --> 01:18:43.500
and my wife upset
every 15 minutes.

01:18:43.400 --> 01:18:45.700
I don't want to hear
another word

01:18:45.700 --> 01:18:48.200
about this boot camp nonsense.

01:18:48.200 --> 01:18:51.000
Dad, look,
with all due respect,

01:18:50.900 --> 01:18:53.000
you really don't have
any say here.

01:18:53.000 --> 01:18:54.300
Oh, yes, I do.

01:18:54.400 --> 01:18:56.500
I earned it when you
dumped her on us this summer.

01:18:56.400 --> 01:19:00.000
This kid needs love
and understanding and patience.

01:18:59.800 --> 01:19:02.100
Do you hear yourself?

01:19:02.100 --> 01:19:05.600
Where was the love and understanding
when I needed it,

01:19:05.500 --> 01:19:08.400
when you let her
run me out of the house

01:19:08.300 --> 01:19:10.100
because she didn't like
my boyfriend?

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:11.900
What? I never threw you
out of this house.

01:19:11.800 --> 01:19:14.200
I simply said you couldn't live here
and do drugs.

01:19:14.100 --> 01:19:16.100
You two have a lot of nerve

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:18.500
bringing my parenting skills
into question.

01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:21.900
Stop it.
Mom, stop talking to them like that.

01:19:21.800 --> 01:19:24.300
Okay, I will go
to the stupid boot camp.

01:19:24.300 --> 01:19:27.600
- No, Greta, Greta.
- Wait wait.

01:19:27.400 --> 01:19:30.300
- Greta's staying here.
- Dad.

01:19:30.200 --> 01:19:32.600
- And so are you.
- No, I'm not.

01:19:32.500 --> 01:19:34.800
We're gonna make this right.
We're gonna fix it.

01:19:34.700 --> 01:19:37.100
We're gonna get to know
one another, this family of ours.

01:19:37.100 --> 01:19:40.100
Dad, I have a job.

01:19:40.100 --> 01:19:43.100
Well, you've got vacation time
saved up, haven't you?

01:19:43.100 --> 01:19:46.100
Well, yeah, but that's for Bermuda
in the fall.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:48.700
Oh, you're taking your daughter
to Bermuda in the fall, are you?

01:19:48.600 --> 01:19:51.600
No, just Edgar and l.

01:19:51.600 --> 01:19:52.700
Uh-huh.

01:19:52.700 --> 01:19:55.600
No, you cannot make Edgar
spend his vacation here.

01:19:55.400 --> 01:19:57.000
Edgar isn't invited.

01:19:57.100 --> 01:19:59.300
This is between us and you
and Greta.

01:19:59.200 --> 01:20:02.700
And if Edgar really loves you,
he can just do without you for a little while

01:20:02.500 --> 01:20:04.100
while you save
your daughter's life.

01:20:04.100 --> 01:20:06.800
When you put it like that,
I have to say--

01:20:06.700 --> 01:20:09.000
- You're not gonna leave me here?
- Yeah.

01:20:09.000 --> 01:20:10.500
You're leaving me here?

01:20:10.400 --> 01:20:12.400
Yeah, this is the best idea
any of us have had.

01:20:12.300 --> 01:20:15.800
You know, I think your dad is right.
This could be good for everyone.

01:20:15.800 --> 01:20:19.000
- Edgar.
- See you in a couple of weeks.

01:20:18.800 --> 01:20:21.500
- Edgar.
- You'll be fine, sweetheart.

01:20:21.400 --> 01:20:23.700
Oh, this is grand.

01:20:23.700 --> 01:20:25.900
Oh, this is gonna really
be helpful.

01:20:25.900 --> 01:20:27.800
Go on, you two, yuck it up.

01:20:27.800 --> 01:20:29.300
I don't even have
any clothes to wear.

01:20:29.300 --> 01:20:31.500
Grandma's got some dresses
you could wear.

01:20:31.400 --> 01:20:34.700
- Edgar: Bye, all.
- You two are exactly alike.

01:20:34.600 --> 01:20:36.500
And you--

01:20:57.500 --> 01:21:00.100
Here.

01:21:00.100 --> 01:21:01.500
Here he is.

01:21:01.400 --> 01:21:03.400
Oh, yeah, there he is.

01:21:07.900 --> 01:21:10.300
He was handsome.

01:21:11.900 --> 01:21:14.900
I dream about him sometimes,

01:21:14.900 --> 01:21:17.300
but he never looks the same.

01:21:18.700 --> 01:21:21.300
You have his eyes.

01:21:21.200 --> 01:21:23.000
Yeah?

01:21:23.000 --> 01:21:24.900
And his brains.

01:21:26.700 --> 01:21:28.800
Well, I'll try to keep mine
inside my skull.

01:21:41.300 --> 01:21:43.400
I always loved
that picture of you.

01:21:43.300 --> 01:21:44.400
God.

01:21:44.500 --> 01:21:47.000
Oh my God.

01:21:46.900 --> 01:21:49.300
What happened to your hair, Mom?

01:21:49.200 --> 01:21:51.100
The 1980s.

01:21:51.000 --> 01:21:53.000
It's huge.

01:21:52.900 --> 01:21:54.900
Katherine:
Big hair. Big hair.

